-- Saudi Rabigh Refining Says Polyethylene Unit Resumes Operations After Fire
-- B y   I n a l   E r s a n
-- 2010-10-18T05:39:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/saudi-rabigh-refining-says-polyethylene-unit-resumes-operations-after-fire.html
Rabigh Refining and Petrochemicals
Co., a joint venture between state-owned Saudi Aramco and
Sumitomo Chemical Co. of Japan, said its polyethylene production
unit resumed operations after a fire. The company made the
announcement in a statement to the Saudi bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Inal Ersan in Dubai at 
